{"markdown":{"containsRefs":false,"markdown":"::: {.question}\n\n**Deleveraging and Share Issuance**\n\n\n```{r}\n#| eval: true\n#| results: asis\n#| echo: false\n#| warning: false\nlibrary(webexercises)\nset.seed(1002)\nshares_outstanding <- round(rnorm(1, mean = 50, sd = 2))\nmarket_cap <- round(rnorm(1, mean = 2.25, sd = 0.5))\ndebt_outstanding <- round(rnorm(1, mean = 756, sd = 1.5))\nshare_price <- market_cap * 1000 / shares_outstanding\nnew_shares_to_issue <- debt_outstanding / share_price\n```\n\n\nCompany Y has `r round(shares_outstanding , 2)` million shares outstanding and a market capitalization of `r round(market_cap, 2)` billion.  It also has `r round(debt_outstanding, 2)` million in debt outstanding. The company plans to **delever completely** by issuing new equity and repaying all outstanding debt.   Assume perfect capital markets.  How many new shares must the company issue (in million)?\n\n::: {.question-block}\n\n<form onsubmit=\"event.preventDefault();\" style=\"display:flex; gap:8px; align-items:center;\"> <label for=\"module7_num_q3\"><strong>New shares to issue (millions):</strong></label> <input type=\"number\" id=\"module7_num_q3\" name=\"module7_num_q3\" style=\"width:160px;\" data-correct-answer=`r round(new_shares_to_issue, 2)` data-tolerance=\"1\" step=\"0.01\" /> </form> <div id=\"feedback-module7_num_q3\" class=\"feedback\" data-status=\"\" style=\"display:none;\"> ✅ New shares = Debt ÷ Price = `r round(debt_outstanding,2)` ÷ `r round(share_price,2)` = <strong>`r round(new_shares_to_issue,2)` million</strong>. </div> \n::: \n::: ","srcMarkdownNoYaml":""},"formats":{"html":{"identifier":{"display-name":"HTML","target-format":"html","base-format":"html"},"execute":{"fig-width":7,"fig-height":5,"fig-format":"retina","fig-dpi":96,"df-print":"default","error":false,"eval":true,"cache":null,"freeze":false,"echo":true,"output":true,"warning":true,"include":true,"keep-md":false,"keep-ipynb":false,"ipynb":null,"enabled":null,"daemon":null,"daemo